overview: The user initiated a project to review and enhance a sleep
  questionnaire application. The agent began by conducting a detailed audit of
  the existing implementation against the provided Statement of Work and
  questionnaire specification. This review highlighted several areas needing
  improvement, which were then prioritized. The first critical task undertaken
  was the integration of a 1-10 severity scale for tiredness interference. This
  involved updating data types, validation schemas, the questionnaire UI to
  include a slider and conditional safety warnings, and both the web and PDF
  report generation to display an urgent safety message if the reported severity
  was high. This ensures that users with severe tiredness are immediately
  alerted to potential risks and advised to seek professional help.
